Welcome!

You are in an AIMMS Example. Feel free to play around and create something more in this app!
 
If you do, please fork this repository and commit your changes. This ensures our GitHub stays up-to-date for the entire community!
For questions that can't be posted on the community, contact us at support@aimms.com.

You can also check our other interactive resources:

  • In the Online Community, talk to other developers and AIMMSians about the product, modeling, use cases, and more.
  • In the Academy, learn new skills and challenge yourself. We are busy creating new courses, so keep an eye out!

Problem

In this practical example, an efficient plan is devoloped for delevering oil tankers which are pre-coupled to a set of cargoes. Prior to the optimization, all feasible routes need to be generated after importing the data. When creating the routes, the loading window of the cargo is taken into consideration, as all cargoes must be delivered on time. Afterwards, each cargo will be allocated to a time-chartered or voyage-chartered vessel within the model. The objective of the model is to determine the minimum costsfor combinations of cargoes and routes. 

Additionaly, the model has some assumptions and constraints. One of these assumptions is thatthe ship can only carry one cargo at a time. Furthermore, it is assumed that all used vessels will go directly to the loading port onethe timehorizon begins. The two constraints are as follows: each cargo can ultimately be transported by only one vessel, and charter vessels can only be assigned to one route at a time.
